INSERT INTO `books_excursion` VALUES (1,'City Tour','3 hours','ex-li-fon-1.png','0','0','<p>During an individual city tour with licenced tour guide you will get to know the history of Rome from the years of its foundation. You will visit Roman forum, Colosseo, valley of 5 antique hills, Capitoline square, Venetian Square, Spanish Steps, Barberini square, Trevi Fountain, Column square, temple of Adrian, antique Panteon and Navona square.</p>','<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\">This city tour can be done by foot or by car. Our meeting point will be at your hotel or in any place in the center of Rome. We will see the <strong>Valley of 5 Roman hills-Capitoline, Palatine, Aventine, Esquilin</strong>e and <strong>Celio.</strong> Along the street of <strong>Roman Forums</strong> are located most antique Roman ruins-Forums of Republican and Imperial times-antique Roman public center&nbsp;that was&nbsp;the place of pagan basilicas, triumphal arches and central city streets.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\">Then we will visit Colosseum and the archeological are of the house of emperor Nerone - Domus Aurea. On the Capitoline Hill we will also see famous buildings of Capitoline Museums and Senat - the&nbsp;renaissance architecture&nbsp;of Michelangelo. After the square of Venice we will continue to Roman barock districts with glamourous fountains - masterpieces of Bernini architecture.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\"><strong>Trevi Fountain, &nbsp;Dolce Vita Street</strong> and <strong>Barberini Square</strong> were mentioned in famous <strong>Fellini</strong> mouvies.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\"><strong>Spanish square</strong> with famous Spanish steps&nbsp;&nbsp;is a famous area as many&nbsp; writers, poets and actors&nbsp; lived there in XVII-XVIII century. Then we are visiting antique<strong> Panteon</strong> that has the history of over 2000 years. Near Panteon is located Navona square that was one time an antique Roman stadium and now a popular place for enjoying evening life music concerts and shows. In the middle of the square - <strong>the Fountain of the Four Rivers</strong> - another mastrepiece of Bernini</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\"><strong>Duration of the tour - 3 hours</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\"><strong><br /></strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\"><strong>Walking tour:</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\"><strong>Cost for 1 - 3 persons</strong>&nbsp;- 110 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\"><strong>Ð¡ost for 4 - 7&nbsp;persons</strong> - 160 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\"><strong>Cost for 7 - 10 persons</strong> - 220 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\"><strong>Mini van or car</strong> - 100 euro per tour&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p><img src=\"../../../../ex_1_image_1.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_1_image_2.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_1_image_3.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_1_image_4.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_1_image_5.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_1_image_6.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /></p>','â¬ 110','0','0'),(2,'City Tour','6 hours','ex-li-fon-2.png','0','0','<p>During this individual tour with private licenced tour guide you will get to know the history of Rome from days of its foundation, will visit Roman Forum and Colosseum, Capitoline square, valley of 5 Hills, Capitoline square, Piazza Venezia, Spanish steps, Trevi fountain, Piazza Colonna, Adrian Temple, Panteon, Navona square, St. Angel Castle. We will also visit St. Peter Basilica in Vatican.</p>','<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Our meeting point is in your hotel or in front of <strong>Colosseum</strong>. The first part of the tour starts in the antique part of Rome -<strong> the Valley&nbsp;of 5 Hills</strong>: <strong>Capitoline,&nbsp;Palatine, Esquiline,&nbsp;Celio</strong> and <strong>Aventine</strong>.&nbsp;We will visit the ruins of antique <strong>Forums</strong> -&nbsp;antique Roman square with&nbsp;pagan temples, Senat, Trajan markets. We will walk along antique streets and will learn a lot of legends and stories about Roman Empire.&nbsp;Then we will visit <strong>Colosseum</strong> - <strong>Amfitheatre of Flavius Emperors</strong> that is one of the wonders of the world. We will see where was the antique stage, gladiators cells and spectators seats. We will take a panoramic look also from upper floors.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Near the Colosseum is <strong>the Arch of Constantine</strong> - the main triumphal arch of Roman Empire. Then we will follow the street of Imperial Forums towards the Venetian Square. We will walk up the famous Michelangelo steps towards the Capitoline Museums and Senat - the architecture of Michelangelo times.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Then we will walk on top of Palatine Hill&nbsp;to explore&nbsp;ruins of <strong>Imperial Palaces</strong> and beautiful <strong>Farnese Gardens</strong>. Behind Palatine Hill is located <strong>Maximus Circus</strong> - that was one time the&nbsp;area for Roman horse racing. We will see <strong>Aventine Hill</strong> with panoramic terrace&nbsp;in the famous Orange Garden and Malta Square from where you can see the so - called Sacred Hole -&nbsp;a hole in the bronze door of Malta monastery through which one can see the view on 3 states&nbsp;- Malta, Italy and Vatican.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">From there we will continue to explore barock districts of Rome with wonderful palaces and fountains.<strong> Trevi Fountain</strong> is just a&nbsp;must for any traveller to Rome. It seems that you are the actor of <strong>\"Dolce Vita\" Fellini</strong> movie. Spanishs steps and Spanish square, decorated with Barcaccia (\"Boat\") Fountain is a masterpiece of Bernini sculpture. We will see the Adrian Temple and <strong>Panteon</strong> -&nbsp;the unique pagan temple that has over 2000 years of history.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Our lunch break will be in a traditional family - type restaurant with Roman cuisine. Cost - around 20 - 25 euros per person including house wine.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">From there we continue to <strong>Navona Square</strong> - the former stadium and now the place with<strong> the Fountain of Four Rivers</strong> and <strong>Saint Agnes Church</strong> and just a lovely walking area!</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Then we will cross <strong>Tiber River</strong> and continue&nbsp;with the&nbsp;visit of Castle Sant\' Angelo&nbsp;- Roman mausoleum of Emperor Adrian and also afterwards papal castle in renaissance centuries. From the top terrace can be seen the view over all Rome.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Then we will visit <strong>St. Peter Basilica</strong> in<strong> Vatican state</strong>. This Cathedral is the grand masterpiece of Bernini barock architecture and the center of christianity.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Duration of the tour - 6 hours</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><br /></strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;Walking tour:</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Cost for 1 - 3 persons</strong>&nbsp;- 250 Ðµuro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Ð¡ost for 4 - 6 persons&nbsp;</strong>-&nbsp;330 Ðµuro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Ð¡ost for 7 - 9 persons&nbsp;-</strong> 350 Ðµuro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>By car:</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><br /></strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Cost for 1 -3 persons - 350 euro</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Cost for 4 - 6 persons - 400 euro</strong></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"../../../../ex_2_1.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_2_2.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_2_3.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_2_4.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_2_5.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_2_6.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_2_7.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_2_8.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /></p>','â¬ 250','0','0'),(3,'Antique Rome','3 hours','0','0','0','<p>During this individual tour with licenced tour guide you get a detailed visit of antique Roman sightes that tell us about historical facts and legends from Roman founders Romulus and Remus till Etruscan, Repubblican and Imperial times. We will visit Colosseum - Roman symbol, Roma Forum, Palatine Hill and other pagan constructions of those centuries.</p>','<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">This is a walking tour. It starts in front of <strong>Colosseum</strong>.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">We visit the archeological area of Rome - <strong>Roman Forum</strong> and <strong>Imperial Forum</strong> - the area with antique streets, squares, pagan temples and triumphal arches. There&nbsp;walked Julio Cesare and other Roman emperors and warriors. In the centre of Forum one can see the place where the Julio Cesare aches&nbsp;are preserved. We will enter into the restored building of Curia - antique Cenat of Rome. Also there are gloriuous triumphal arches: Septimius Severo, Tito and Costantine. Near the Vestaile Vergin Temples there was recently restored the house where Vestailles lived. Forums was&nbsp;the place for public gathering&nbsp;and meetings that were called Comitiums. We will talk about legends, stories, rumours of Roman Empire. Also, there is a lot to know about Roman feasts, celebrations, rituals, beliefs&nbsp;and every day life of those days.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">Near the Forum there is the <strong>Mamertine prison</strong> where Peter and Paul were imprisoned before the execution.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">Then we will climb on top of Palatine Hill where Romulus put down the first stone for the foundation of Eternal City. Perhaps there was Lupelcarium - the place where legendary she - wolf brought them up. And then there emperors construlted there residences. From the top pf Palatine there opens up a great view to Aventine and Gianicolo Hills</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">The best place to take photos of Colosseo is from Oppio Hill where was a house of Nerone - Domus Aurea. This place was badly ruined after the fire of Rome in 64 AD.&nbsp;Colosseo was constructed on what was before the garden of Nerone and where stayed legendary Colossum of Nerone - the huge statue.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">We will then enter into <strong>Colosseo - Flavius Amfitheatre</strong> constructed in 72 - 80 AD. We will see the stage place, gladiator and wild animal cells and recently excavated under stage ruins. The upper floors have a panoramic terrace with the view on all this area.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Duration of the tour - 3 hours</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Cost for 1 - 3 persons</strong> - 120 Ðµuro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Cost for 4 - 7 persons</strong> - 170 Ðµuro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Cost for 7 - 10 persons</strong> - 265 euro</div>\r\n<p><img src=\"../../../../ex_3_1.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"../../../../ex_3_2.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"../../../../ex_3_3.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_3_4.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_3_5.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_3_6.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_3_7.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_3_8.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','â¬ 120','0','0'),(4,'Antique Rome','4,5 hours','0','0','0','<p>During this individual tour with licenced tour guide you will get a detailed visit of sightes connected with history of eternal city - from founders Romulus and Remus till Roman emperors. You will learn about historical heroes and legends connected to those times. We will visit archeological area of Roman Forus, Colosseum, Palatine Hill, Imperial Forums, Domus Aurea of Nerone, Marcello Theatre, Circus of Massimo and Bocca della Verita</p>','<p style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">This is a walking tour and it starts in front of <strong>Colosseum.</strong> During this tour we will learn in details about pagan customs and traditions, glorious history of Roman empire and every day life of those days.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">We start with the visit of the archeological area of Rome - famous<strong> Roman Forum</strong> - historical ruins of Reppublican and Imperial times of Roman history. We will walk along the same Roman streets - Via Trionfale e via Sacra where Roman emperors and heroes walked. In the centre of Roman Forum is located the central antique square of Rome where waqs burned down the body of Julio Ceasar and are concerved his historical ashes - Area di Cesare. We will see lots of ruins pagan Basilicas - Basilica Aemilia, Basilica of Divo Julio, Temple of Vestal Vergins, Temple of Romulus, Temple of Castor and Pollux. Also the famous arches - Arch of Tito, Settimio&nbsp; Severo and Costantine. We will visit the building of Curia where was located the place of Roman Cenat. There was the area of public sppeches - Comitium and Rostrums.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">Near to the Forum we will visit <strong>Mamertine Prison</strong> where St. Peter and Paul were&nbsp;their executions.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">Then we will proceed to climb up to the Palatine Hill where Romulus put down the antique stone of Eternal City and where later lived Roman Emperors. We will see the ruins of their palaces, built in times of Emperor Augustus and Flavians that still have mosaics, columns and porticos. Also from Palatine top can be seen the great view to Aventine and Gianicolo Hills.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">Then we will visit Colosseum. We will learn about the history of Nerone that lived in the historical Domus Aurea that was there before the famous fire of Rome in 64 AD. Colosseum or Favians Amphitheatre is one of the wonders of the world - the place of gladiator battles.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">Going around Palatine Hill we will reach <strong>Massimo Circus</strong> - a huge antique races stadium where now are going on the excavations. Then we will reach the embankment of Tiber river where once was Forum Boarium - meat market. Also, there is a curious Tiberina Island - once an antique port and now a popular place for a walk. Near by are also well preserved pagan temples - Vestal Vergins and Fortuna Verilis</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">Near the wall of <strong>Santa - Maria - in - Cosmedin Church</strong> one can see the legend of Rome - <strong>\"The Mouth of Truth\"</strong> - a marble head that represents Ocean or River. In Middle Ages there was a belief that if one told a lie his hand will be cut off. A famous Hollywood movie \"Roman Holiday\"&nbsp;made it very famous.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">Before reaching Venetian Square we will see the ruins of <strong>Theatre of Marcellus</strong>- the only remaining theatre in Rome constructed under Augustus Emperor in 23 BC.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Duration&nbsp;of the tour: 4,5 hours&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Cost for 1 - 3 persons</strong> - 170 euro</div>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Cost for 4 - 7 persons</strong> - 220 euro</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Cost for 8 - 12 persons</strong> - 300 euro</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"../../../../ex_4_1.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_4_2.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_4_3.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_4_4.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_4_5.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_4_6.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_4_7.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_4_8.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_4_9.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /></p>','â¬ 170','0','0'),(5,'Vatican State','0','0','0','0','<p>With individual licenced tour guide you will visit Vatican State - St. Peters\'s Basilica that was built of the place that was once Nerone Circus where Apostle Peter was crucified. We will visit papal art collection in Vatican Museums - the largest museum in the world that contains art, paintings, tapestries, sculptures. Sistine Chapel where sacred conclave historically is on when pope is elected. Michelangelo frescos are world masterpieces. It is also possible to arrange the additional visit of Vatican gardens.</p>','<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>We meet at your hotel or in the center of St. Peter\'s square.</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Vaticano - Stato della Citta del Vaticano</strong> - is a separate religiuos state located within the state of Italy. The State is located on the land of 44 hectars (110 acres) with the population of approximately 800 persons. It is the smallest state in the world. It was officially divided from Italy in 1929 when popes signed Lateran Agreement with all the rules and regulations of the State. From 756 till 1870 popes ruled in&nbsp;the centre of Italy, combining religious and civil power- this land was called Sacred Papal State. The State now is ruled by pope Benedetto XVI.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">On the territory of Vatican are located many buildings: St.Peter\'s Basilica, Apostolic Palace - the official residence of pope, Sistine Chapel and Vatican Museums and also many other parts of the state that can not be visited by the public. For exemple Vatican Gardens can be visited only on the prior booking.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">We start with the visit of Vatican Museums. Pinacoteca contains artwork of famous italian painters from renaissance to barock periods. You will see the works of <strong>Giotto, Rafael, Guido Reni, Caravaggio.</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">In the famous building of eight-corner courtyard you will see the sculpture of Laocoonte with sons that was the first marble art work&nbsp;excavated&nbsp;during the ruling of&nbsp;pope Julio II in 1506. Also, Apollo Belvedere - the prefered sculpture by Michelangelo. In the gallery of Flamish Gobelens you will be amazed by the \"perspective effect\" and well preserved colours of these mastrepieces. Then we will see geografical maps of all Italy painted by scientists of XVI century.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">The most famous frescos are by Rafael and Michelangelo. We will see Stanze of Rafaello where Julio II comitioned special religious subjects for the frescos of those&nbsp;cardinal meeting rooms. In the former Borgia appartments there is now modern art section: Van Gogh, Mark Shagal, Matis and&nbsp;Salvador Dali works.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;Of course, the unique part of the museum is the Sistine Chapel. The walls were painted by Perugino, Botticelli and Rosselini while Michelangelo painted the ceiling and the alter - \"Creation of the World\" and \"Last Judjment\".</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;Throug the door&nbsp;from the Sistine Chapel to St.Peter\'s Basilica we will have the unique exit to Scala Regia where we will see swiss guards. The first&nbsp;Cathedral construction was&nbsp;done in 324 to 349 and the first ceremonies were held already in 326. During&nbsp;centuries around the Cathedral grew up the Holly City with monks and pilligrims houses, chapels, monastries. The Cathedral was reconstructed many times under the project of Rafael, Michelangelo and then Bramante, Bernini and&nbsp;Boromini. We will also see Vatican grotto - the lower room where popes were berried. Now the tomb of pope&nbsp;John Paul II is located in the room of the Cathedral as he was canonized in May 2011.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<strong>Cost for 1 - 3 persons</strong> - 130 euro</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Ð¡ost for 4 - 7 persons</strong> - 170 Ðµuro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Cost for 7 - 10 persons</strong> - 220 Ðµuro</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><img src=\"../../../../ex_5_1.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_5_2.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_5_3.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_5_4.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_5_5.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_5_6.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_5_7.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_5_8.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_5_9.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /></p>','â¬ 130','0','0'),(6,'Rome - from Renaissance to Barock','0','0','0','0','<p>During this individual tour you will visit glamourous palaces, fountains and squares decorated in XVII - XVIII century -masterpieces of such grand masters as Bernini, Bprromini, Maderno, Valadier. We will see Barberini square, Dolce Vita Street, Cappuchin Crypt, Spanish steps, Barcaccia fountain, Trevi Fountain, Piazza Colonna, Adrian Temple, Panteon, Santa Maria Sopra Minerva Church, Piazza Navona, Campo dei Fiori, Piazza Farnese</p>','<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">This tour starts at your hotel or at Piazza Barberini.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Rome is a unique city where are located masterpieces of&nbsp;many artistic periods: antique, medievil, renaissance and barock. Starting with Barberini square we will see Triton fountain - the masterpiece of Lorenzo Bernini that created lots of architectural ensembles in the centre of Rome on the order of pope Urban VIII Barberini. From there we can have a walk along the famous DolceVita Street that was described in Fellini movies. We will have a look into Santa - Maria - della - Concezione Church that is famous for the Capuchin Cript where monks were berried.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Following&nbsp;Sistina street we will reach the top of Pincio Hill from where there is a view to Spanish Square and Spanish Steps. We will walk down along&nbsp;Spanish steps and take wonderful fotos near Barcaccia (Boat) Fountain - another Bernini masterpiece. This part of Rome was famous for writers, poets and musicians that lived there once and now it is a place to see Italian fashion brands. There are 3 streets that one can visit: Babuino, Corso and Ripetta - all with wonderful shopping occasions. All these streets form a famous triangle - Tridente - and&nbsp;lead to Popolo Square with its sculptures done by architect Valadier.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;From there is a short walk to our next spot -&nbsp;Trevi Fountain&nbsp;surrounded by typical straight Roman street. This place is always crowded and one throws a coin as a traditional believe in order to come back to Rome. Also there we will taste the best Italian home - made ice cream - gelato.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;Alfter the Column Square we will go to visit Panteon - antique Roman pagan temple and then next to it Santa - Maria - Sopra -Minerva Church that&nbsp;was built in 1280 - 1370&nbsp;over the place that was once Minerva Pagan temple. Architectural changes and redecorations in the 1500s and 1900s stripped it of some of its magnificence, but it still includes an awe-inspiring collection of medieval and Renaissance tombs. Papal inquisitions were held there. We will see renaissance frescos by Filippino Lippi in carafa Chapel, statue by Michelangelo and many chapels in barock style.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;Our next stop is at Navona square with&nbsp;the Fountain of Four Rivers&nbsp;- the grand Bernini sculptures that represent 4 continents. Next to Navona square there is Campo de Fiori - Flower Market square - a curious disctrict that has nice pubs and local restaurants. Farnese square is next to is with renaissance and barock facades.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Duration: 3 hours</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Cost for 1 - 3&nbsp;persons</strong> - 120 euro&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Cost for 4 - 7 persons</strong> - 160 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Cost for 7 - 10 persons</strong> - 220 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Car or mini van</strong> - 100 euro per tour</div>\r\n<p><img src=\"../../../../ex_6_1.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_6_2.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_6_3.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_6_4.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_6_5.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_6_6.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_6_7.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_6_8.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /></p>','â¬ 120','0','0'),(7,'Christian Rome','0','0','0','0','<p>This tour offers you the visit of Roman jubileo basilicas - Santa Maria Maggiore, San Giovanni in Laterano, San Paolo fuori le Mura and also other churches with important christian relics. On Celio Hill we will see antique Baptisterio and Scala Santa, Santa Croce in Jerusalem, San Pietro in Vincoli. In Santa Prassede and Santa Sabina were berried christian martyrs.</p>','<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">This tour is done by car.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Rome is called \"second Jerusalem\"- the city to explore cathedrals, churches, chaples with christians relics and symbols. There are approximately 500 christian religious places in Rome. Visiting these places one will learn not only the history of Eternal city but also life stories&nbsp;of grand painters and architects. Every churÑh is a unique masterpiece of art. One admires wonderful&nbsp;architecture and&nbsp;visits christian relics -&nbsp;remains of apostles and christian martyrs.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Rome is visited by millions of pilgrims. By antique tradition pilgrims did a visit of 7 churches - they went around main christian basilicas and prayed on the relics to get an indulgence. In the year of 1300 pope Boniface VIII made this tradition&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Jubilee </span>- a special year of remission of&nbsp;sins and universal pardon. In Christianity Jubelee year is every 25 years. There are 4&nbsp;papal Basilicas - St. Peters\'s, St. Paul, S. Maria Maggiore, St.John Lateran that have bronze Jubelee doors that are open on Jubilee year.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">We start with the visit of Esquiline Hill where is locÐ°ted S. Maria Maggiore Basilica. The legend tells that it is built on the place where was a miracolous snowfall in summer. The interior is famous for medieval ceiling and mosaics, Sistine Chaple where pope Sisto V is berried, Paolina Chapel. In the altar is located the relic - the <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Holy Crib</span>, which was carried to Rome by Christian refugees during the Muslim conquest of the Holy Land in the 7th century.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Next to it we will visit Basilica&nbsp;of Santa Prassede that contains relics from Roman catacombs brought during the times of pope Pashalio I (817-824). There are magnificent 9th century mosaics and relic of Christ\'s scourging column.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Santa Pudenziana Chuch is dedicated to Praksida and Pidenziana - Roman martyrs. Below the crypt were berried christian relics.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Another Basilica on Esquiline Hill is Saint Peter in Chains (San Pietro in Vincoli) where under the main altar are kept Peter\'s chains that were on him during his imprisonment in Mamertine prison. Also, there is Michelangelo statue of Moses - part of tomb of pope Julius II.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Then we continue to Lateran district - once it was a place where popes&nbsp;built up their residences&nbsp;after the begining of christianization in Rome in 313. After fires of 1307 and during Avignon papacy no palaces survived. In XVI Ñentury pope Sisto V built up Sancta Sanctorum - the chapel where was placed the icon of Jesus Christ the Savior. In the same building there are Holly Stairs - wooden steps that encase white marble steps where Jesus feet walked over to praetorium of Pilate at Jerusalem.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">St. John Lateran was constructed in this area in IV century and then after many reconstructions it was rebuilt by Bernini. Next to it is Lateran Baptistry where emperor Costantine I had been baptized.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Another Basilica - Holly Cross in Jerusalem - is also on of 7 piligrimage Basilicas of eternal city.&nbsp;There is the collection of&nbsp;relics from Holly Land and a replica Shroud of Turin.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Then we will leave Aurelian walls and will reach St.Paul\'s&nbsp;Basilica dedicated to apostle Paul. &nbsp;We will admire medallions - portraits of all popes and wonderful interior with marble, lapis and malachite stones.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Then we will continue to Aventine Hill - the most pittoresque and quiet hill from all antique valley. There is a curious Santa Sabina Basilica that was constructed in V century and it still has original mosaic floors, corinthian columns. On Malta square we will see famous Holly Door to 3 states - Italy, Malta and Vatican.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">On this tour it is possible to see St.Peters\'s Cathedral in Vatican for those that do not have a separate Vatican tour.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">During visit to the churches it is a must to cover your knees and shoulders.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Duration - 3 hours</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Ð¡ost for 1 - 3 persons</strong> - 120 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Cost for 4 - 7 persons</strong> - 160 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Cost for 7 - 10 persons</strong> - 230 euro</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Car</strong>&nbsp;<strong>or mini van-</strong> 100 euro for the tour</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><img src=\"../../../../ex_7_1.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_7_2.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_7_3.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_7_4.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_7_5.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_7_6.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_7_7.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_7_8.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /></p>','â¬ 120','http://maps.google.ru/maps?saddr=Basilica+di+S.Maria+Maggiore&daddr=Santa+Prassede+to:Santa+Pudenziana+to:San+Pietro+in+Vincoli+to:Sancta+Sanctorum+to:San+Giovanni+in+Laterano+to:Croce+in+Gerusalemme+to:Basilica+di+San+Paolo+fuori+le+Mura+to:Basilica+di+Santa+Sabina&hl=ru&sll=41.877985,12.49578&sspn=0.05496,0.111494&geocode=FR5NfwIdNbi-ACFCuyKFaJKxlg%3BFT5JfwIdl7i-ACGM6E-237vNww%3BFXRRfwIdbau-ACGI6oEqUhsJqg%3BFWo_fwIdK6C-ACEw1Kvkdtw7Mg%3BFaYlfwIdNda-ACHb_jqw8hzXMA%3BFSclfwIdiM--ACGxOYOOQHo7og%3BFa0tfwIdl_O-ACEh5de4ZcbugiknB9_Ck2EvEzEzpXg9w88Kog%3BFZiwfgId0mO-ACE64JcSTZ0TAA%3BFfoafwIdu22-ACGBTnIUAxE_kQ&vpsrc=0&dirflg=w&mra=ls&t=m&z=14','0'),(8,'Catacombs of Rome - subterranean secrets','0','0','0','0','<p>An exciting individual visit of Via Appia Antica - the most important Roman Imperial road that connected Rome to Greece, Egypt and Asia. Along the road we will see ruins of villas and tombs of reppublican and imperial times, midieval castles and ruins. During this tour we also visit San Callisto and San Sebastiano Church catacombs with relics of II - IV centuries BC.</p>','<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">This tour is done by car.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">We will leave Rome and after passing by Colosseum and baths of Caracalla we will&nbsp;drive away from&nbsp;Aurelian Walls from where stars antique Appian Road. The entrace to this road is through antique Sebastian gate.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">This road is named after Appius Claudius Caecus, the Roman censor who began and completed the first section as a military road to the south in 312 BC. It connected Rome to Brindisi, Apulia and all south of Italy. This road was the first long road built specifically to transport troops outside the smaller region of greater Rome and it had also importance in trade development. Therefore it was called \" main imperial road\". On the most antique part of the road we will see antique Roman black stones - the way Roman layed all their roads. Also, along this road Romans built up aqueducts - water supply, imperial palaces, tombs, mausoleums.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">There is Qua Vadis church that is built on the place that according to the legend is considered to be the point where Apostle Peter met the vision of Jesus Christ when he was escaping from Roman persecutions. Peter asked Jesus : Domine Qua Vadis (Jesus, where are you going?). Jesus replied: Eo Roman iterum crucifigi ( I am going to Rome to be crucified again). This miracolous meeting made Apostle Peter come back to Rome and continue his christian deeds. In the middle of this church we will see a copy of&nbsp;marble stone where feet of Peter steped over. The original one is conserved in St. Sebastian Church that we will visit. It also has a relic of this martyr.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Appian Road is famous for catacombs - ancient human made subterranean passageways for religious practice and berrial places that form kilometres of underground corridors in this area. There are more that 5 entraces to underground areas and the temperature there&nbsp;is always 14 - 15 degrees Centigrate.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">We will descend to St.Sebastian catacoms where are conserved original christian frescos representing Jesus crib, Virgin Mary in parayer, Last supper and other symbols.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">There is another vast catacomb of St. Callisto. This complex was formed during II - IV BC. During early christian years monk Callisto was taking care after these tombs and we will see his relic. There were also berried many other monks and St. Cecilia -&nbsp;Roman martyr that were executed during her prayers.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; When we return back to Rome from Appian road&nbsp;we will visit St.Clement\'s chuch. It is unique in Rome because it has&nbsp;3 time levels: twelfth - century church with wonderful altar mosaics, fourth - century basilica and a real Roman house with pagan temple of 1 BC. Really amazing chance to travel back in time and explore Roman secrets! There are relics of St. Clemente and St. Cyrillus.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;The next church with catacoms is St. Agnese outside Walls. It was built by pope Honorius I in 7 century BC on the place where St. Agnese was originally berried.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Santa - Maria - in - Cosmedin Church&nbsp;in the centre of the city&nbsp;that is famous for the legendary \'Mouth of Truth\" marble mask and a relic of St. Valentine&nbsp;has also subterranean necropolis.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Duration - 3 hours</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Cost for 1 - 3 persons</strong> - 120 Ðµuro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Cost for&nbsp;4-7&nbsp;persons</strong> - 160 Ðµuro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Cost for&nbsp;7-10&nbsp;persons</strong> - 230 Ðµuro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Car or mini van</strong> -&nbsp;100&nbsp;euro per tour</div>\r\n<p><img src=\"../../../../ex_8_1.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_8_2.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_8_3.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" />&nbsp; <img src=\"../../../../ex_8_5.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_8_6.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_8_7.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_8_8.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_8_9.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /></p>','â¬ 120','0','0'),(9,'Rome by night','0','0','0','0','<p>During this tour you will see Eternal city with unique evening lights. We will see Roman Forum, Imperial Forum, Colosseo, city squares, fountains, panoramic hills. Capitoline Hill, Venezia square, Trevi fountain, Piazza Colonna, Adrian Temple, Piazza Navona, Campo di Fiori, Tiberina Island, Ganicolo Hill, St. Angel Castle, Quirinal Palace, Reppublica square</p>','<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">This tour can be done by foot or by car.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">We start at Capitoline Hill where from the upper&nbsp;terrace we will have a magnificent view&nbsp;on Roman Forum - the antique center of Rome. It has a special view as the evening starts and it is not yet too dark.&nbsp;Around Capitoline Hill there are other four main hills of Rome - Palatine, Aventine, Esquiline and Celio. The famous Capitoline square has famous Michelangelo ensemble - Campidoglio and Capitoline Museums. We will walk along the original steps of Mihelangelo\'s cordonata that lead us down to the&nbsp;ruins of&nbsp;Roman house of I century AD.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;On Venetian Square the building of Altare delle Patria has a different look in evening lights and then we will drive along Roman forums - Foro Romano and Imperial Forum with Trajan\'s column. We will have a stop by Colosseum and Costantine arch to take special evening fotos.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">After driving around Palatine Hill and Circus Massimo - antique&nbsp;chariot racing&nbsp;stadium we will drive on top of Aventine Hill where travellers admire the so - called Sacred Hole through which one can see throung the hole in the&nbsp;bronze door of Malta monastery the dome of St. Peter Catherdal. It is the so- called \"view to three states\": Italy, Malta and Vatican. Travellers really like it!</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">Driving along Via del Corso we will continue to the so-called Roman barock districts that have magnificent squares with fountains. We will stop by Trevi fountain - the unique XVII century masterpiece by Nicola Salvi that is built on the place where once Roman aqueduct arrived. It represents Neptune and other water symbols. Near by is Barberini square with Triton fountain. We can have a cup of coffee in one of the cosy cafees of Via Veneto - Dolce Vita Street mentioned in Italian movies.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">Then we will visit Spanish square with Spanish steps. It is in the area of Pincio Hill from where Borgese park starts (Villa Borgese). Once many writers, poets, composers and generally foreign travellers liked to settle down in this&nbsp;area of Rome. On top of Pincio Hill there is Trinita dei Monti Church. We will see Barcaccia fountain (Boat)- also Bernini\'s artwork. There are 3 streets that form a so - called Trident that ends up on Popolo square.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">Navona square that once was Domitian\'s stadium and now is a popular place for life music, clowns, restaurants and cafees. The main attraction is Bernini\'s&nbsp;Fountain of the Four Rivers and the church of Sant\'Agnese in Agone by Borromini.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">Near by is Campo de Fiori that once was the city market area and now has best wine bars, restaurants and local shops open till late.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">In the second part of the tour we will explore the other side of Tiber river. There is a curious island on the river called Isola Tiberina with small bridges on both sides, then Trastevere district stars on the other shore of the river. Trastevere&nbsp;means Trans Tiberem - beyond Tiber river. This is&nbsp;the&nbsp;district of many restaurants&nbsp;with the best local food in family owned restaurants.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">We will drive drive up Gianicolo Hill - the tallest hill from all seven Roman hills. The view from there is just breath taking. There is also Acqua Paolo - the fountain built by pope Paolo V Borgese. From there when we descend we will see St. Peter\' s dome in evening lights and Castel Sant\' Angelo.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Duration - 3 hours</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Cost for 1 - 3 persons</strong> - 140 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Cost for 4 - 7 persons</strong> - 190 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Cost for 7 - 10 persons</strong> - 200 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Car</strong> - 100 euro per tour</div>\r\n<p><img src=\"../../../../ex_9_1.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_9_2.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_9_3.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_9_4.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_9_5.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_9_6.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_9_7.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_9_8.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /></p>','â¬ 140','0','0'),(10,'Angels and Demons - Rome by Dan Brown','0','0','0','0','<p>During this individual tour you will feel yourself a hero of Den Brown novel \"Angels and Demons\". We will follow the same itinerary as Robert Lengton did discovering the mysterious signes of illuminators society: Santa - Maria - del - Popolo Church, St. Peter\'s Cathedral, Santa Maria della Vittoria Church, St. Angelo Castle.</p>','<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Duration - 3 hours.</strong> This tour is done by car.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">During this tour we will follow the same route as heroes of Dan Brown movies did&nbsp;- the&nbsp;Path of Illumination, solving puzzles and enigmas, decoding secret messages hiden in Bernini sculptures and misterious texts. We will see&nbsp;beautiful squares of Rome, fountains, catacombs, underground passages&nbsp;and different sites where pagan and christian symbols are mixed together. The path of Illumination includes: Santa Maria del Popolo church, Piazza del Popolo, Saint Peter\' s square, Santa Maria della Vittoria church, Piazza della Minerva, Piazza Navona and Castel Sant\' Angelo</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">What is the movie about? In Rome in 1600 during the papal election there are happening strange events. The secret influentiel&nbsp;anti religious society of Illuminated was born. They promise to put the end to Vatican existence with a bomb that is placed in St. Peter\'s basilica and will soon explore. Also, four cardinals - candidates to papal post disappeared and Illuminated promised to kill them.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Professor Robert Langdon (played by actor Tom Hanks)&nbsp;is travelling around Rome trying to discover secrets of Illuminated signs so that Vatican will be saved. He finds 4&nbsp;\"markers\" connected with Land, Air, Fire and Water and also sculptures of Bernini that give him necessary indications.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Santa Maria del Popolo church</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">This church belongs to Order of Saint Augustine. It has wonderful Caravaggio masterpieces in one of the chapels.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Role in the film: This church is connected with the sign of Land. There are many berrial places of Roman cardinals and aristocrats. Robert Langdon and his friend Victoria are sure that here they will find there the&nbsp;body of the first cardinal that was killed. Bernini sculpture in Chigi Chapel Habakkuk and the Angel is one of four \"markers\" leading to an ancient Castel Sant\' Angelo.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>St. Peter\' s Square</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">The biggest square in Rome created by Bernini&nbsp;in 1656 - 1667 has a famous colonade that consists of 4 rears of doric columns and is decorated with 140 figures of saints. In the centre of the square there is the Egyptian obelisc brought to Rome by Emperor Kaligula.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Role in the film: The second cardinal according to the film was burnt down in front of St. Peter\'s basilica. This square is conected with the sign of Air. On the marble floor in the middle of the square we will see the face of the angel blowing air in the easten direction. It becomes the second \"marker\" for professor Langdon.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Santa Maria della Vittoria Church There is the famous Bernini sculpture&nbsp;Santa Teresa that is dedicated to Spanish monk Teresa that lived in XVI century. The sculpture tells the story that once angel came to her and&nbsp;pierced her heart with a long spear of gold, then drew it out and left her with the a great love of God. Role in the film: Cardinal Guider was tied up above the altar of Santa Maria della Vittoria Church and was burnt alive. Therefore this church is connected with the sign of Fire. After seeing the statue of Santa Teresa professor angels\'s spear indicted next directions - to south - west.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>The fountain of Four Rivers</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">This fountain was designed by Gianlorenzo Bernini in 1648 - 1651 for Pope Innocent X whose family palace - Palazzo Pamphili faced onto Navona square. The fountain represents four rivers of four continents through which papal authority had spread. Nile represents Africa, Danube - Europe, Ganges -Asia, Plate - America.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Role in the film:</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">This fountain is connected with the sign of Water in the film. Professor arrived just in time before the kidnapped cardinal was dumped in the water. But the fountain is not much more than a foot deep. He saved him from death. The last \"marker\" is the dove on the obelisk that points out to north - east - Castel Sant\' Angelo.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Castel Sant\' Angelo&nbsp;</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><br /></strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Once the Castle was an imperial mausoleum, then a medival prison and later papal residence. Now it is a Roman museum from where one can see a nice view to the city. The castle was connected with Vatican by pasetto - a corridor of 800 metres long through which popes could get away in case of invasions.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Role in the film:</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Castel Sant\' Angelo was the place where Illuminators had their headquarters and where the killer was hiding</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Also, Sistine Chapel in Vatican is shown in the film during the papal election.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">We will also visit Panteon - the temple of All Gods built up in 27 AD where heroes of the movie also happen to be in the beginning of the film.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Cost for 1 - 3 persons</strong> - 120 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Cost for 4 - 7 persons</strong> - 160 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Cost for 7 - 10 persons</strong> - 220 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Car</strong>&nbsp;<strong>or mini van</strong>- 100 euro per tour</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><img src=\"../../../../ex_10_1.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_10_2.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_10_3.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_10_4.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_10_5.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_10_6.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_10_7.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_10_8.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_10_9.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_10_10.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_10_11.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /></p>','â¬ 150','0','0'),(11,'Roman life - feel yourself Roman','0','0','0','0','<p>This is a relaxing walking tour to most quiet and folclore parts of Rome where you can feel real every fay life of Romans with all its colours and styles. We will see Campo de Fiori district where in the morning there is flower and fruit market and in the evening there are lovely restaurants and pubs open till late. We will walk along Tiberina island to get to Trastevere district and to explore its narrow streets with lovely decorated houses and local shops.</p>','<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Duraion - 2, 5 hours</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">This is a walking tour that will take us to the most hidden non - turistic spots of eternal city.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">We will start at Panteon and after visiting this famous pagan temple we will take side streets through to Sant\' Eustachio square with the best Roman coffee that we will taste. Sant\' Eustachio church has cosy interior. Near by is the building of Sapienza - Roman University and we will see Fountain that represents Books attached to the wall of the building.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Next stop is on Navona Square with Bernini&nbsp;Four Rivers Fountain&nbsp;and Santa - Agnese - in - Agone church.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Argentina Square where we will have a look at ruins of Pompey Theatre (Area Sacra) - the first stone built theatre in Rome that dates back to 55 AD. Exactly in this place Julius Caesar was killed. And now there are&nbsp;famous Roman cats that leave next to these ruins.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Taking Jiubbonari Street that means street of Jacket - makers we will reach Campo de Fiori - the centre of local life and entertainment. Originally there lived handicraft makers - hats, clothes, bags, shoes, keys and so on. So, the streets have such names as indication of what they produced. There are nice local restaurants, vinneria (wine pub), and shops open without break and till very late. Here we can taste gelato - home made ice cream.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Then we will cross Tiber river by Fabrizio bridge and we will visit Tiberina island. The island is shaped like a boat. Crossing Cestio bridge we will find ourselves in Trastevere district. Via della Scala will bring us&nbsp; to Piazza Santa - Maria - in Trastevere that is always full with young people, students and visitos. In the centre of the square there is a nice fountain built by architect Fontana in 1692.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Santa - Maria - in - Trastevere church was built up in 340 but the actual look is the mixture of&nbsp;that of XII - XIX centuries. On the facade there is the original&nbsp;mosaic of&nbsp;XII century&nbsp;that represents Virgin Mary and&nbsp;Jesus Christ&nbsp;. Also inside the church there are a number of late XII century mosaics by Pietro Cavallini on the subject of the life of the Virgin. The 22 granite columns of ionic and corinthian orders came from the ruins of Baths of Caracalla. There is also the icon of VII century.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">We will visit Roman Museum in Trastevere that shows a lot of local folclore and every day life details of Romans of previous centuries.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Cost for 1 - 3 persons</strong> - 100 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Cost for 4 - 7 persons</strong> - 160 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Cost for 7- 10 persons</strong> - 190 euro</div>\r\n<p><img src=\"../../../../ex_11_1.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_11_2.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_11_3.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_11_4.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_11_5.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_11_6.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_11_7.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_11_8.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_11_9.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /></p>','â¬ 100','0','0'),(12,'Raffaello and Michelangelo in Rome','0','0','0','0','<p>During this individual tour we will discover palaces, churches, squares of Rome that were designed by great Renaissance Masters - Raffaello and Michelangelo. We will visit Villa Farnesina, Sant Eligio deglli Orefici Church, Santa Maria della Pace, Sant Agostino, Santa Maria del Popolo, San Pietro in Vincoli, Santa Maria sopra Minerva, Santa Maria degli Angeli and Capitoline Square ensemble.</p>','<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">We will visit sites, monuments and buildings created by painter and architect Raffaello Sanzio&nbsp;in Rome.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">We will visit <strong>Church Sant\' Eligio - degli - Orefici</strong>, located on historical Via Jiulia that was originally construcled according to the project of Raffaello. It was mostly frequented by the comunity of jewelers (the name orefici means jewelers)</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Church Santa -Maria - della - Pace</strong> that was constructed by Roman architects Bramante and Pietro da Cortona. In Chigi Chapel there are famous frescoes by Rafael&nbsp;representing four SibÑls - prophetess</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">In <strong>Sant\'Agostino Church</strong> there is one fresco representing prophit Isaia.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\">The masterpiece of renaissance architecture is Villa Farnesina constructed on the order of the banker A. Chigi. &nbsp;Actually, Chigi introduced Raffael to the papal court. The interior was painted by&nbsp;Peruzzi and S. del Piombo. Rafael painted the fresco&nbsp;\"Triumph of Galatea\"&nbsp;and other frescos on the subject of Cupit and Psichy. In 1577 this villa was bought by cardinal Farnese. Now there is Lincei Academy located there.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Santa - Maria - del - Popolo church</strong> is built on the place that is considered to be a tomb on emperor Nerone. In 1099 pope Pashalio II ordered to through into Tiber river his remains and to built over it a christian church. Many renaissance painters decorated it: Pinturicchio, Caracci, Raffael, also many architects such as Bernini, Bramante and Sansovino. The Chigi Chapel where Chigi brother are berried was constructed according to Raffael\'s project. Also, the mosaic in the dome is done according to the cartoon of Raffaello.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Then we will visit sites, monuments and buildings created by architect, painter and sculpturer Michelangelo.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>San - Pietro - in Vincoli Church</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Pilligrims always visit it as it has the relic of Peter\'s chains. In this church there is the Tomb - statue of pope Julio II that is called Moses.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Capitoline Square</strong> was fully made according to Michelangelo design starting from the drawing of the floor up to facades of the buildings and staircase shape. He planned the statue of Mark Aurelio to be in the middle of the square. There are 3 palaces: Palazzo Senatori, Palazzo Conservatori and Palazzo Nuovo. There are also two antique Roman statues of Castor and Pollux that were excavated in Pompei Theatre.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>The Farnese Palace</strong> near Campo de Fiori now houses the Embassy of France. Therefore one can not visit it inside. The palace was built for the cardinal Alessandro Farnese who later became pope Paolo III.&nbsp; Michelangelo took part in the decoration of the facade along with other architects: A de Sangallo, G. della Porta.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Santa - Maria - sopra - Minerva Church</strong> is one of the few gothic churches in Rome. It is built on the place that once was Minerva Godess temple. There is Michelangelo statue Jesus Christ carrying the Cross.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Santa - Maria - degli - Angeli Church</strong> was created on the place of antique bath house and Michelangelo took part in the project during 1563 - 1568.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Porta Pia</strong> is a gate in north - eastern part of Rome near antique Aurelian walls. Nometana Street starts from this gate. They were&nbsp;constructed by Michellangelo on the order of pope Pius IV from Medici familiy.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Duration: 3, 5 hours</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Cost for 1 - 3 persons</strong> - 130 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Cost for 4 - 7 persons</strong> - 170 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Cost for 7 - 10 persons</strong> - 230 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Car</strong>&nbsp;<strong>or mini van</strong>- 100 euro per tour</div>\r\n<p><img src=\"../../../../ex_12_1.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_12_2.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_12_3.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_12_4.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_12_5.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_12_6.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_12_7.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_12_8.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /></p>','â¬ 130','0','0'),(13,'Bernini and Borromini in Rome','0','0','0','0','<p>During this individual tour we will visit palaces, squares and fountains that were designed by main barock masters - Giovanni Lorenzo Bernini and Francesco Borromini. We will see Piazza Barberini, Spanish steps, Navona square, San Carlo alle Quatro Fontane Church, Sant Andrea al Quirinale church, Sant Andrea delle Frate, Sant Ivo alla Sapienza, Sant Agnese in Agone, San Giovanni dei Fiorentini. And, of course magnificent barock fountains.</p>','<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">This tour starts at Barberini square. This tour is done by car.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">Once this square was a centre of papal and aristocratic Roman life. In the centre of the square there is the <strong>Triton Fountain</strong> (1643) - masterpiece of Bernini. It has a perfect water supply system that has 360 years of history</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">In the corner of <strong>Barberini square</strong> there is <strong>Fontana delle Api</strong> - was constructed on the order of pope Urban VIII and it represents his coat of arms. The Barberini Palace (1625 - 1633) where once this pope lived also has his coat of arms representation on the facade. It was constructed by great Roman masters such as Carlo Maderna, Borromini and Bernini. The unusual &nbsp;shell - shaped staircase was projected by Bernini. Once inside the palace there was his private theatre, library and gobelen workshop. Now it houses <strong>National Gallery of Antique Art</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">Following Via Quattro Fontane (Four Fountains street)&nbsp; we will see four fountains that represent rivers: Tiber, Arno and godesses Diana and Juno. From this point one can see three Roman obeliscs in fronts of&nbsp;Santa Maria Maggiore, Trinita dei Monti and Quirinale Palace.&nbsp;There is the <strong>church San - Carlo - alle - quattro - Fontane</strong> constructed on the project of Carlo Borromini in the middle of XVIII century. It is so tiny inside that it is called San Carlino. The interior design can be called \"superbarocco\" - there&nbsp;are no flat surfaces in the interior&nbsp;but everything is curved inside. Following Quirinale street along a long wall that is called Manica Lunga and it is part of Quirinale Palace where&nbsp;one can see presidential guards as right now Italian president lives there.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">Then we will visit&nbsp;<strong>Sant - Andea - al - Quirinale Church</strong> ( project of Bernini , De Rossi and Boromini in 1671)</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">From there we will go in&nbsp;the direction of <strong>Spanish Steps</strong> - Scalinata della Trinita dei Monti - one of the pittoresque places in Rome. There are always many young people and tourists around. There is also Spanish Embassy near by due to the&nbsp;fact that this area was so popular among spanish travellers that settled down in Rome or travelled around Italy. Many writers, poets, composers lived there.&nbsp; In the centre of the square there is Barcaccia Fountain created by Pietro Bernini in 1629.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">Propaganda Fide Palace created during the reign of pope Urban VIII&nbsp;for the catholic university and typography&nbsp;was projected by Bernini and Borromini together.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Sant - Andrea - delle - Fratte Church</strong> was created in the area where in XVII century were suburbs of the city. The ceiling, dome and tower were created by Borromini. Inside one can see original statues of angels that Bernini did for Sant\' Angelo Castle. They were ordered by pope Clement IX and he desided to keep them inside the church forever</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Sapienza Palace</strong> (building of XV century)&nbsp;&nbsp;for the Roman University was reconstructed by Michelangelo and Giacomo della Porta&nbsp;in XVI century. The University was founded by pope Bonifacio VIII in 1303. Right now it houses state archives. In the courtyard there is <strong>Sant - Ivo - alla - Sapienza Chuch</strong> (1642 - 1650) - a very interesting mastrerpiece of Borromini. It has a shape of a bee reminding about pope Barberini coat of arms. On top of the construction there is an unusual onion - shaped cupola decorated with a cross.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">During emperor Flavio Domiziano reign on the place where now there is <strong>Navona square</strong> was a stadium of Domitian for water battles. During pope Innocenzio X this square got&nbsp;its actual look. This pope ordered the construction of <strong>Pamphili Palace</strong> in XVII century for the wife of his brother - Olimpia Pamphili. Near by there was created <strong>Sant - Agnese - in - Agone Church</strong> dedicated to Sant Agnese - a christian marter that was&nbsp;beheaded&nbsp;by pagans on this place. Inside the church there are conserved her relics and also the tomb of pope Innocenzo X. The facade was decorated by Borromini in 1652 - 1655.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">In front of the church there is <strong>Four Rivers Fountain</strong> - masterpiece of Bernini. The figures represent four continents: Nile, Ganges, Danube, Plate. There is a legend that one of the figures is covering the face with its hand as if it does not want to face the facade of Borromini \'s Sant - Agnese Church as these two architects were in competition. There are two other fountains - <strong>Fountain of Neptune</strong> and <strong>Fountain of Moro</strong> on the sides of the square.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">There is a district in Rome where many Florentine people lived. There is <strong>Via Giulia</strong> street that is 1 kilometer long and it was planned in the middle of this district by Bramante on the order of pope Jiulio II in the beginning of 1500. It was planned to connect Vatican with Capitoline Hill.and it was the first straight street in Rome. <strong>Saint - Giovanni - dei - Fiorentini Church</strong> was constructed by Da Sangallo and Carlo Maderno in&nbsp;1620. Borromini planned the altar. Borromini and Maderno are berried there.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">Then we will cross&nbsp;Tiber river to get to Trastevere district.<strong> San - Crisogono Church</strong> in the begining of Viale Trastevere street was created over the place that was once a house of a Roman who was beheaded during Deocliziano persequtions. The tower of the church looks like a medieval castle. We will see XIII century ceiling and cosmatesco marble&nbsp;floor. <strong>Poli Chapel</strong> was created by Bernini. There is a crypt of V century.</div>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">In the centre of <strong>Saint - Franceso d\'Assisi square</strong> there is Saint - Francesco - a Ripa Church dedicated to the place where he stopped by when he travelled in Rome in 1219. His original crussifix is conserved in the crypt. There is Bernini statue -&nbsp;Beata Ludovica Albertoni (1625)</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Duration&nbsp;- 3,5 hours</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Ð¡ost for 1 - 3&nbsp;persons</strong> - 130 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Cost for 4 - 7&nbsp;persons</strong> - 170 Ðµuro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Cost for 7 - 10&nbsp;persons</strong> - 230 Ðµuro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Car or mini van</strong>&nbsp;- 100 euro per hour</div>\r\n<p><img src=\"../../../../ex_13_1.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_13_2.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_13_3.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_13_4.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_13_5.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_13_6.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_13_7.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_13_8.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /></p>','â¬ 130','0','0'),(14,'Caravaggio in Rome','0','0','0','0','<p>During this individual tour we will visit churches where art works of great italian painter Michelangelo Merisi da Caravaggio are. Caravaggio was a great art reformer of XVII century, the painter of strong religious and realistic subjects. We will visit San Agostino Church, San Luigi dei Francesi, Santa Maria del Popolo.</p>','<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">This is a walking tour that starts in Piazza del Popolo</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">We will visit&nbsp;<strong>Santa - Maria - del - Popolo Church</strong> that is built on the place that once was the tomb of emperor Nerone. In medieval age pope Pashalio II ordered the remains of Nerone to be thrown to Tiber river and to built a church over the&nbsp;tomb place.&nbsp;Many renaissance&nbsp;painters took part in church decoration: Pinturicchio, Caracci, Raffaello and also architects: Bernini, Bramante and Sansovino. The main altar is decorated with the painting of XIII century -Madonna del Popolo. In <strong>Cerasi Chapel</strong> there are two paintings by Caravaggio: <strong>Conversion of Saul, Crucifixion of Apostle Peter</strong> and Assemption of Virgin Mary by Caracci.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\">Then we&nbsp;will&nbsp;follow Ripetta Street that is then contnued by Via della Scrofa (that means pork street)&nbsp;where are many&nbsp;local food shops such as bakeries, meat and wine shops.&nbsp;There is San - Luigi - dei - Francesi Church&nbsp;that was built specially for the local french comunity. In one of the chapels there are paintings by Caravaggio: <strong>Apostle Matfei with Angel, Conversion of&nbsp;Apostle Matfei and Martyr of&nbsp;Apostle Matfei</strong>.&nbsp;These are classical Caravaggio art works with famous light and dark technique.</div>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Then we will visit <strong>Sant\' Agostino Church</strong> that is located in the same district. In one of the chapels there is Madonna di Loreto by Caravaggio.</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\"><strong>Duration: 2, 5 &nbsp;hours</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\"><strong><br /></strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\"><strong>1 -3 persons - 110 euro</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\"><strong>4 - 7 persons - 150 euro</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\"><strong><br /></strong></div>\r\n<p><img src=\"../../../../ex_14_1.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_14_2.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_14_3.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_14_4.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_14_5.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_14_6.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_14_7.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /></p>','â¬ 110','0','0'),(15,'Borghese Gallery','0','0','0','0','<p>During this tour you will visit a unique Borgese art gallery that contains sculpture and paintings from Scipione Borghese former private collection. We will see wonderful sculpture of Bernini that were commitioned by pope Paul V for his nephew Scipione, paintings by Raffaello, Caravaggio, Titian and many other painters of Venetian, Florentine and Roman schools of XVI - XVII century.</p>','<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">We are meeting up in front of the entrance to the <strong>Borgese Gallery</strong>. It is necessary to prebook the entrance ticket 2 - 4 days in advance.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">On the first floor we will find the most famous sculptures of Bernini and paintings by Caravaggio. There are the following Bernini sculptures: <strong>Rape of Proserpina, Apolo and Dafna, David. Also, Antonio Canova statue - Paolina Bonaparte as Venere. &nbsp;</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Caravaggio is very well represented by: <strong>Madonna Palafrenieri, David with the Goliath\' s head, Young sick Baccus, Young boy with a basket of fruit</strong> and many others.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">The other paintings are on the second floor: Tizian- &nbsp;Sacred and Profan love, Raffaello - Descend from the cross, Domenicino - Diana\'s hunt, Rubens - Pieta. Also, there are flamish and dutch schools.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">After the tour we will have a&nbsp;walk in the park - very&nbsp;pittoresque XVII century landscape type of park in Rome.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Duration: 2 hours</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>1 -3 persons - 100 euro</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>4 - 6 persons - 130 euro</strong></div>\r\n<p><img src=\"../../../../ex_15_1.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_15_2.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_15_3.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_15_4.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_15_5.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_15_6.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_15_7.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_15_8.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /></p>','â¬ 100','0','0'),(16,'Capitoline Museums','0','0','0','0','<p>During this tour you will visit one of the world famous sculpture museum. The collection was started by pope Sisto IV in 1471. It was the first world private collection that was open for the public visit. The museum is located on Capitoline square - wonderful ensemble of Michelangelo architecture.</p>','<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">We are meeting up in front of the statue to Marco Aurelio in the middle of <strong>Capitoline square</strong>.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Capitoline museums are located in two buildings: <strong>Palazzo Nuovo</strong> and <strong>Palazzo Conservatori.</strong> There is the connection between these buildings through Tabularium corridor.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">In the Palazzo Nuovo we will see the collection of antique Roman sculpture such as portraits of Roman emperors, Venere Capitolina statue, wounded Amazon, Amore and Psichy, Satire and other world famous items</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">In Palazzo Conservatori we find Capitoline she - wolf (the bronze of V century AD), the Boy with Thorn (Spinario), parts of colossus of Costantine Emperor, Venere Esquilina, Herculus and other Roman and Greek items.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">There is also Capitoline museums pinacoteca where one can see masterpieces of Tiziano, Guido Reni, Caravaggio, Rubens, Paolo Veronese</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Duration - 2 hours</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><br /></strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Cost</strong>: 50 euros per person</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Minimum - 3 persons</strong></div>\r\n<div><strong><br /></strong></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;<img src=\"../../../../ex_16_1.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_16_2.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_16_3.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_16_4.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_16_5.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_16_6.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /></div>','â¬ 150','0','0'),(17,'Picture Galleries in Rome','0','0','0','0','<p>During this individual tour you will visit famous picture galleries of Rome: Barberini Palace, Doria Panfili Gallery, Corsini Gallery, Spada Gallery.</p>','<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">We are meeting up by Triton fountain in the middle of Barberini Square.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">In Barberini palace we will visit <strong>the National Gallery of Ancient Art</strong>. Among many masterpieces of Italian and international painters of XII - XVII centuries we will see famous Fornarina by Raffaello, paintings by Fra Angelico, Pomarancio, Bronzino, Coreggio, Guido Reni, Poussin, Van Dyck, Caravaggio, Tintoretto, Tiziano.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">In Doria Pamphili Palace on Via del Corso there is <strong>Pamphili Gallery</strong> that was once a private art collection of noble Pamphili family from Genova. We will see paintings by Tiziano, Lotto , Caravaggio and others</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">In Corsini Palace there is <strong>National Corsini Gallery.</strong> There are masterpieces by Rubens, Van Dyck, Murilio, Caravaggio, Guido Reni and Beato Angelico.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">Spada Palace was decorated by Borromini who was a friend to one of cardinals of Spada family. Borromini created a very famous gallery with perspective - it has the illusion of a long gallery but actually it is only 7 metres long. In Spada Gallery we will see works of Rubens, Tiziano, Caracci and Guido Reni.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Duration - 3, 5 hours</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Cost for 1 - 3 persons</strong> - 170 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Cost for 4 - 7 persons</strong> - 200 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Cost for 7 - 10 persons</strong> - 270 euro</div>\r\n<p><img src=\"../../../../ex_17_1.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_17_2.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_17_3.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_17_4.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_17_5.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /></p>','â¬ 170','0','0'),(18,'Sculpture Galleries in Rome','0','0','0','0','<p>Durin this individual tour you will visit sculpture museums in Rome: Massimo Palace, Altemps Palace, Baracco Museum, Museo di Roma.</p>','<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>We will meet up at your hotel.</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Palazzo Massimo.</strong> <span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">This museums houses the most important collection <span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">of classical art. <span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">This palace stands on the place where once was a villa of Peretti that was constructed by pope Sisto V and it belonged to Massimo family. On the first floor there are Roman original sculptures of II century AC - II century DC. These were the centuries of big development in Rome when Roman empire was at its peak. On the other floor of the museum there is antique decorative art. The unique part of the collection are the frescos that were excavated in Lazio and Pompei. There are also egyptian mosaics that represent animals and nature. There are items from Villa Julia - the former palace of Augustus daughter married with Agrippa. Inside the museum you can see underground ruins of the room of Livia - wife of emperor Augustus.</span></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Altemps Palace.</strong>&nbsp; <span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">It is a renaissance palace in the center of Rome that houses the beautiful collection of Ludovisi. <span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">A legendary collection of&nbsp;the Boncompagni Ludovisi princes, families of popes and cardinals who keep in the rooms and gardens of their beautifull roman house a multitude of ancient statues; a crowd of Gods, fauns, satyrs, ninphes, athletes and warriors.</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><br /></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">Among the masterpieces displayed, we&nbsp;will admire&nbsp;the Ludovisi throne, one of the most famous piece in the collection - &nbsp;it shows Venere\'s birth. And also, the famous group of Oreste and Elettra, embracing and saying goodbye to each other, milestone for entire generations of sculptures. Behind the brightness&nbsp;of the sculptures and paintings is hidden a tragedy that left to Altemps Palace the fame of a damned place: Cardinal Altempsi made the mistake to give in marriage his son Roberto with one of the Orsini, a family in hatred to the pope Sisto V, who in revenge, accused Roberto of adultery, and cut off his head.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Baracco Museum.</strong> <span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">It houses the former private collection of Barome Giovanni Barracco that contains egyptian, greek, roman sculpture. There are also libraries inside the museum. </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Museo di Roma</strong> is colated in Braschi Palace that was constructed for cardinal of pope Pius V. It houses more than 40 000 items of art such as paintings, sculpture marble items and mosaics.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\"><strong>Duration: 3, 5 hours&nbsp;</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\"><strong>Cost for 1 - 3 persons</strong> - 170 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\"><strong>Cost for &nbsp;4 - 7 persons</strong> - 200 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\"><strong>Cost for 7 - 10 persons</strong> - 270 euro</div>\r\n<p><img src=\"../../../../ex_18_1.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_18_2.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_18_3.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_18_4.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_18_5.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_18_6.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /></p>','â¬ 170','0','0'),(19,'Tivoli - Villa d \' Este, Villa Adriana, Villa Gregoriana','0','0','0','0','<p>You will visit an antique city of Tivoli located in Lazio region, at the bottom of Apenine mountains, 24 kilometres away from Rome. There is the Unesco archeological complex of Adriana Villa located in wonderful park and Villa d\' Este - renaissance construction with unique park with fountains. Villa Gregoriana was built on the shore of Aniene river.</p>','<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">This tour is done by car. We start from your hotel. Driving time up to Tivoli - 45 minutes. Tivoli is a small town in Lazio region&nbsp;located about 30 kilometres east - north of Rome. Both Villa D\' Este and Villa Adriano are Unesco Heritage monuments.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">In ancient times Tivoli was called Tibur and it was connected to Rome by antique road - Via Tiburina. According to the legend Tivoli was found&nbsp; 1 century before Trojan war by brothers Tibur, Katillon and Karas. Latium population made Tibur a developed and florishing town. It was famous for olive oil and fruit plantations, pottery production and travertine stone excavations. Travertine is the famous stone that was used for Colosseo decorations. According to mythology Herculus was the antique protector of these lands.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">At first we will visit <strong>Villa Adriano</strong> <span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">that was built by emperor Publi Gelio Adriano in 118 - 134 BC and it is an exceptional complex of classical Roman buildings that combine the best elements of the architectural heritage of Egyypt, Greece and Rome. The space of villa itself is 120 ga located on the land of 300 ga of the park. We will see rooms of Small and Big bath houses with floor mosaics, exedra rooms, unique Canopa, ninfeo, Latin and Greek libraries, Imperial Palace and Golden square. Maritime Theatre is a&nbsp;private appartment area&nbsp;of Hadrian is very well preserved.</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Villa d\' Este</strong> <span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">was built by cardinal Ippolit d\' Este - the son of famous Lucrezia Borgia and Alfons d\' Este. It was buikt in 1549 as from 1550 Ippolit d\' Este was the governor of Tivoli. Cardinal chose lovely Valle Gaudente - Valley of Joy for creation of a unique renaissance gardens that had a profound influence on the&nbsp; development of garden design throughout Europe. Gardens descend from the villa to a flat terrace in the manner of amfitheatre and have lovely grottos, cascades, nishes and even a musical fountain! The fountains are operating all year round. </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Villa Gregoriana</strong> was created on the shores of Aniene river near the rocks of Katillo mountain. The park located at the feet of the city\'s ancient acropolis was commissioned by pope Gregory XVI in 1835 to rebuilt the bed of the Aniene river which had been damaged by the flood of 1826. Since ancient times the river formed a wide curve around the acropolis after which it fell from a limestone\' s spur into the plain below. The river formed originally four falls, now reduced in two. We will visit grottos of Neptune, Sirens, Valerio bridge,&nbsp;Vestalle Vergins Temple&nbsp;and Valio Vopisco Villa&nbsp;built in 114 AC</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Duration - 5 - 6 hours </strong>with possible lunch stop</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Cost including car for 1 - 3 persons</strong> - 330 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Cost includig car for 4 - 7 persons</strong> - 380 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><br /></strong></div>\r\n<p><img src=\"../../../../ex_19_1.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_19_2.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_19_3.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_19_4.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_19_5.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_19_6.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_19_7.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_19_8.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_19_9.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /></p>','â¬ 330','0','0'),(20,'Lake Bracciano - Castello Orsini - Odescalchi','0','0','0','0','<p>One of the largest vulcanic lakes in Lazio region is Bracciano. Medievil catle of Orsini - Odescalchi is located on the shore of this lake. It was built by counts Orsini in XIII century. You wil see unique interiors and hear about secrets and legends of those times.</p>','<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\">This tour is done by car. The town of <strong>Bracciano</strong> is located 30 kilometres away in the direction north - west from Rome. The population of this town is 15, 500 people.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\">On the shore of the lake Bracciano we will visit a very well preserved medievil castle built in XIII century by Orsini noble family and then resold after their bankruptcy to Odescalchi family in XVII century. Right now it is still owned by one of the princesses of Odescalchi family.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\">In 1481 pope Sisto IV was hiding there during plague epidemie in rome and 16 years later it was attacked by papal troops headed by Giovanni Borgia - son of pope Alexander VI. In 1558 Paolo Giordano Orsini got married with the daughter of Cosimo Medici and he got the title of Count of Bracciano.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\">There were celebrated famous marriage ceremonies of <strong>Tom Cruise</strong> and<strong> Eros Ramazzotti</strong>.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\"><strong>Duration: 3 hours</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\"><strong>Cost for 1 - 3&nbsp;persons</strong> - 170 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\"><strong>Cost fo 4 - 6&nbsp;persons</strong> - 265 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"justify\"><strong>Car</strong> - 185 euro per tour</div>\r\n<p><img src=\"../../../../ex_20_1.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_20_2.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_20_3.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_20_4.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_20_5.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /></p>','â¬ 170','0','0'),(21,'Roman castles - gourmand tour','0','0','0','0','<p>You will visit towns in the suburbs of Rome - Castelgandolfo, Frascati, Ariccia and Nemi lake. Besides natural beauty we will enjoy tasting of local seasonal products - porchetta ham, mushrooms, strawberries. We visit wine and olive plantation, learn about the production process of Frascati wines and stop over at gourmet lunch offered by the owner. These places are great to visit all year around.</p>','<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">This tour is done by car.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">This is the tour to Roman castles -&nbsp;suburban towns near Rome and it is done by car.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Ð¡astel Gandolfo</strong> is a small town 15 miles south - east of Rome on the Alban hills.&nbsp;It is best known as the summer residence of pope. According to the legend&nbsp;in pre - roman age there was&nbsp;the famous Alba Longa capital of mythical Latin League, a city founded by Ascanius, the son of Aeneas. Exactly here was conseved the sacred flame of Vestalle vergins that was brought by Ascanius from captured city of Troya. During republican times many patrician summer residences were established there. The biggest villa was Villa of Domitian that embraced a large territory. In medieval times the territory of Castel Gandolfo became the property of counts of Tusculum and in the early&nbsp;XI century beacem part of the Abbey of San Nilo Grottaferrata.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">The Apostolic Camera with pope Paul V started major public works including a water pipeline to the castle and founding a Reformed Franciscand monastery.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">The Apostolic Palace of Castel Gandolfo is the main attraction of this town. It is in XVII century building designed by Carlo Maderno for pope Urban VIII.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Frascati.</strong> It is a town located 12 miles south - east from Rome on the Alban Hills. From Roman times Frascati was called Tusculum that indicates the fact that it was populated by etruscans. Telegon, the son of Odisseo and Zerera built up the walls of the castle in IX century AD. During republican times this place was populated by patricians that built up villas. In renaissance and barock times there were built villas of Boncompagni, Aldobrandini, Panfili, Borgese decorated nby such architects as Giacomo della Porta, Carlo Maderno and Giovanni Fontana.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><span><strong>Ariccia.</strong> <span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">It is a town on Alban hills. It is a region that was extremely important in Roman and pre - Roman mythology and religion because it was associated with goddess Diana&nbsp;and the god Vibrius. It was one of the oldest cities of ancient Latium that had pagan temples, bath houses, squares and public buildings. After barbaric invasions of X - XVII centuries it was under the control of various counts and dukes. During the pope Alexander VII architect Gian Lorenzo Bernini created Santa Maria Assunta Church. In modern times Ariccia has become famous for its porchetta (pork) and special local wine. We will have lunch in a local restaurant.</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><span>The town of <strong>Nemi</strong> <span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">in Roman times was&nbsp;sacred land due to&nbsp;Diana temple where many pilligrims arrived from Rome and other towns. It has wonderful view on vulcanic lake of Nemi surrounded by pittoresque forests. In July there is strawberry festival and locals make a parade wearing original costumes.</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Duration: 4 hours</strong></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Cost for 1 - 3 persons</strong> - 170 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Cost for 4 - 7 persons</strong> - 250 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\" align=\"left\"><strong>Car</strong> - 185 euro per tour</div>\r\n<p><img src=\"../../../../ex_21_1.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_21_2.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_21_3.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_21_4.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_21_5.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /> <img src=\"../../../../ex_21_6.jpg\" alt=\"\" align=\"left\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"5\" /></p>','â¬ 170','0','0'),(22,'Rome for children','0','0','0','0','<p>Exciting visit for your kids while adults enjoy museums of Rome. Visit of water parks, zoo, etc. Can be done just for kids or accompanied by parents.</p>\r\n<p><a class=\"name\" href=\"http://rome-excursions.com/i1895.html\">\"Rome for children\"</a></p>','<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">During this tour we will visit the most interesting sites for child\'s leasure and relax activities in Rome. In case the location is outside Roman center&nbsp;car with driver needs to be rented - 50 euro per hour</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">The duration of this tour depends on the number of places that we want to visit.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Rainbow MagicLand</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Via della Pace, loc. Pascolano</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Valmontone (30 kilometres away from Rome)</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">10.00- 18.00</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">July - August&nbsp;10.00 - 23.00</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">entrance for adults&nbsp;- 35 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">entrance for children&nbsp;- 28 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">This is a huge entertainment park located on the space of 600 000 m2 with more than 35 types of amusement activities. Also there is Pixie Village - the place for very small children. Maison Houdini - is the amazing underground town for big and small visitors.</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Esplora </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Via Flaminia, 82, Roma</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">entrance to the museum&nbsp;at 10.00, 12.00, 15.00, 17.00</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">closed on monday</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">entrance&nbsp;- 7 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">This is a city - museum for children</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Giardino Zoologico di Roma - ÐÐ¾Ð¾Ð¿Ð°ÑÐº</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Piazzale del Giardino Zoologico, 1. Villa Borgese</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">9.30 - 18.00</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">entrance for children&nbsp;- 10,50 euro,&nbsp;entrance for adults&nbsp;- 12,50 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">A spaciuos zoological garden located in a wonderful Roman park - Villa Borgese will surprize you with lots of types of anumals, fishes and birds</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Technotown</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Via Lazzaro Spallanzani, 1 </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">10.00 - 18.00</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Entrance&nbsp;- 6 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Closed on monday</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">This museum is interesting for children from 10 to 17 years old who are interested in new technologies</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">3 D Rewind Rome</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Via capo d\'Africa 5 </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">9.00 - 19.00</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Adult ticket&nbsp;- 15 euro,&nbsp;children ticket&nbsp;- 8 euro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">You will enjoy historical films in 3 D and 5 D formats - feel like you are Roman!</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Water amusement parks:</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Aquapiper </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Via Maremmana Inferiore Km 29,300 00012 Guidonia (RM) - 20 kilometres from Rome</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Open&nbsp;from 15&nbsp;may&nbsp;till 15&nbsp;september 09.00 - 19.30</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Adult ticket&nbsp;- 16 euro,&nbsp;children - 10 Ðµuro, children below 10 years old free entrance</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Aquafelix</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Via Terme di Traiano Localit&agrave; Casale Altavilla<br />00053 Civitavecchia Nord (Roma)</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Road&nbsp;Ð 12 Rome - Civitavecchia, uscita Civitavecchia Nord, via Terme di Traiano</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Ðpen from&nbsp;12&nbsp;june&nbsp;till 5 september&nbsp;10.00 - 18.30</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Adult ticket&nbsp;- 20 Ðµuro,&nbsp;children ticket&nbsp;- 17,50 Ðµuro</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Fontevivola</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Parco Acquatico Fontevivola - SS 2 Cassia km.50 - Fontevivola</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">A huge amusement park both for adults and children</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Ð¾pen&nbsp;from 10&nbsp;june&nbsp;till 10 september</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Entrance&nbsp;- 20 Ðµuro</div>','â¬ 190','0','0');
